quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,154,"Then{1} We gave Moses the Scripture, making complete [Our favor] upon the one who did good [i.e., Moses] and as a detailed explanation of all things and as guidance and mercy that perhaps in the meeting with their Lord they would believe.",footnotes:1:[Meaning "additionally" or "moreover," not denoting time sequence.]
  6,155,"And this [Qur’ān] is a Book We have revealed [which is] blessed, so follow it and fear Allāh that you may receive mercy."
  6,156,"[We revealed it] lest you say, "
  7,64,"But they denied him, so We saved him and those who were with him in the ship. And We drowned those who denied Our signs. Indeed, they were a blind people.{1}",footnotes:1:[For a more detailed account, see 11:25-48.]
  7,65,"And to the ʿAad [We sent] their brother Hūd. He said, "
  7,66,"Said the eminent ones who disbelieved among his people, "